| clazz = com.fluidops.iwb.widget.PieChartWidget
}}
==== Examples ==== 

===== Bounce multi-colored =====
<source> 
{{#widget: PieChart | 
 input = 'organisation'
 | colors = {{ '#07BF41' | '#1E8099' | '#F7D709' | '#59DEE0' | '#F97D2A' | '#F265F2' | '#69EF74' }}
 | query = '
    SELECT ?organisation ?projects WHERE { 
        VALUES (?organisation ?projects)
        { 
          ("Organisation 1" 27)
          ("Organisation 2" 56)
          ("Organisation 3" 33)
          ("Organisation 4" 23)
          ("Organisation 5" 20)
          ("Organisation 6" 5)
   } }'
 | startEffect = 'bounce'
 | output = {{ 'projects' }}
 | styling = 
   {{ height = '300'
    | width = '400'
   }}
}}
</source>

{{#widget: PieChart | 
 input = 'organisation'
 | query = '
    SELECT ?organisation ?projects WHERE { 
        VALUES (?organisation ?projects)
        { 
          ("Organisation 1" 27)
          ("Organisation 2" 56)
          ("Organisation 3" 33)
          ("Organisation 4" 23)
          ("Organisation 5" 20)
          ("Organisation 6" 5)
   } }'
 | colors = {{ '#07BF41' | '#1E8099' | '#F7D709' | '#59DEE0' | '#F97D2A' | '#F265F2' | '#69EF74' }}
 | output = {{ 'projects' }}
 | startEffect = 'bounce'
 | styling = 
   {{ height = '300'
    | width = '400'
   }}
}}

===== Donut =====
Defined as above but with '''innerRadius''' set to 60.


{{#widget: PieChart | 
 input = 'organisation'
 | innerRadius = '60%'
 | colors = {{ '#07BF41' | '#1E8099' | '#F7D709' | '#59DEE0' | '#F97D2A' | '#F265F2' | '#69EF74' }}
 | query = '
    SELECT ?organisation ?projects WHERE { 
        VALUES (?organisation ?projects)
        { 
          ("Organisation 1" 27)
          ("Organisation 2" 56)
          ("Organisation 3" 33)
          ("Organisation 4" 23)
          ("Organisation 5" 20)
          ("Organisation 6" 5)
   } }'
 | startEffect = 'bounce'
 | output = {{ 'projects' }}
 | styling = 
   {{ height = '300'
    | width = '400'
   }}
}}
===== Colors and links for pie slices =====

You can set a color and a link explicitely for a certain pie slice adding a couple of definitions in the corresponding settings file. To enable links in pie charts set the ''enableLinks'' parameter in the widget configuration to ''true''. Here is an example of the pie slices settings and the chart:

<source>	
"slices": [
		{ 
			"title": "Error",
			"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Error",
			"color": "#F44809"
		},
		{ 
			"title": "Warning",
			"url": "/search/?queryLanguage=SPARQL&queryTarget=default&repository=default&query=select distinct * where{?s ?p ?o} limit 5",
			"color": "#F7D709"
		},
		{ 
			"title": "Info",
			"url": "/search/?queryLanguage=SPARQL&queryTarget=default&repository=default&query=select distinct * where{?s ?p ?o} limit 5",
			"color": "#7DB61C"
		}
	]
</source>

{{#widget: PieChart | 
 enableLinks = true
 | input = 'slice'
 | query = '
    SELECT ?slice ?value WHERE { 
        VALUES (?slice ?value)
        { 
          ("Error" 27)
          ("Warning" 56)
          ("Info" 79)
   } }'
 | settings = 'Settings:pie.custom.links.colors'
 | output = {{ 'value' }}
 | styling = 
   {{ height = '300'
    | width = '400'
   }}
}}

Look in [[Help:SettingsGallery | Chart Settings Gallery]] for more chart examples.